&lt;p&gt;Recap of this week in the revolution: Gross incompetence on display in Signalgate, some law firms capitulate while others defend the law, Greenland says, &amp;#39;Make America Go Away,&amp;#39; and DOGE cuts cost the federal government half of the budget left over after military, social security, medicare, and medicaid spending. More people are detained and deported without cause or due process, and DeSantis proposes using child labor to fill the gap. Join the revolution by taking part in the April 5 &amp;#39;Hands Off&amp;#39; National Day of Action wherever you live.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;section class=&quot;block the-good&quot;&gt;
    &lt;h4&gt;The Good...&lt;/h4&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
            The minority party has more power than you may think...if they choose to use it &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.justsecurity.org/109454/congress-minority-toolbox/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.justsecurity.org/109454/congress-minority-toolbox/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
                &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;U.S. House of Representatives party makeup, 119th Congress&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; src=&quot;/images/PYhVrekYvN-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;103&quot;&gt;
                &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;U.S. House of Representatives 1/3/2025: 218 Republicans, 213 Democrats, 4 vacant seats&lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;It may seem like Democrats have no power because they do not hold the majority in either the House or Senate, but that&#39;s not exactly true.&lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;There are many tools the Democrats could use to obstruct or deny Republican actions, but only if they use them skillfully and coordinate with one another.&lt;/p&gt;
