      &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;New Hampshire resident Fabian Schmidt was detained by U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement and &quot;violently interrogated&quot; in inhumane conditions. Schmidt is a permanent legal resident with a green card in good standing. His abuse apparently came when his green card was &quot;flagged&quot; for unknown reasons.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Schmidt is only one of many legal residents in the United States who are being attacked by the Trump regime on false charges. Many foreign nationals, whether residents of the U.S. or visitors, have reported being detained and abused by immigration officials for no valid reasons. &lt;/p&gt;
