            &lt;p&gt;This seems to be the new status quo: The people who might possibly stand up to the Trump regime have all proven to be remarkably apathetic. In this article, acting SSA commissioner Dudek essentially sums up his own actions with this phrase: &quot;I work for the president. I need to do what the president tells me to do.&quot; It&#39;s worth noting that acting director of the SSA is not a position Dudek is trained for or actively sought out. In fact, he never thought he would hold such a role, which may help explain, but not justify, why he isn&#39;t resisting.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;This is oddly reminiscent of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W8OFrDQkfjM&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Schumer&#39;s sudden flip&lt;/a&gt; on last week&#39;s CR when he suddenly decided that giving in to the Republicans would somehow put them in a position where they would have to start negotiating with Democrats.&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;I am not calling this a conspiracy, but if this were a James Bond movie, you know the only possible explanation would be that the &quot;bad guys&quot; had some sort of mind control device that they were using to keep potential agitators under control.&lt;/p&gt;
