            CNBC host risks career to call Trump&#39;s economic policies what they are: &quot;Insane&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cnREyCAaMtU&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Donald Trump ran for president in each of the last 3 elections largely on the claim that the United States should be run by a businessman instead of a politician.&lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;The problem is that Donald Trump is a terrible businessman. He has no idea how to run a business, as indicated by the economic policies he is advancing right now, which can only be described as &quot;insane.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
