&lt;section class=&quot;block info&quot;&gt;
  &lt;h4&gt;Keeping you informed...&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
          Why did we need to create DOGE to save money? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GupyEudjdNw&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;It must be because we never had a way of identifying and stopping fraud, waste, and abuse in our government before, right?&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;Wrong. The paltry savings that DOGE has created are just random cuts, and have nothing to do with eliminating fraud, waste, or abuse. But there have always been people in our government who &lt;i&gt;really&lt;/i&gt; find and eliminate fraud, waste, and abuse. And they&#39;re good at what they do. Or, at least they were, before they were fired.&lt;/p&gt;
