          &lt;p&gt;U.S. District Judge William Alsup tells the Office of Personnel Management to rescind its directives to fire probationary employees in the Department of Veterans Affairs, the National Park Service, the Small Business Administration, the Bureau of Land Management, the Department of Defense, and the Fish and Wildlife Service.&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;OPM does not have authority to fire employees from other agencies. Defense attorney&#39;s argued that OPM was merely asking the other agencies to terminate employees, but Judge Alsup felt that the speed at which the terminations took place made it all too apparent that this was an order.&lt;/p&gt;
